title: Google\Cloud\ServiceDirectory\V1beta1\Service
name: Service
description:
An individual service. A service contains a name and optional metadata.

A service must exist before [endpoints][google.cloud.servicedirectory.v1beta1.Endpoint] can be added to it.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.servicedirectory.v1beta1.Service

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Immutable. The resource name for the service in the format 'projects/*/locations/*/namespaces/*/services/*'.

params.name: data.metadata
params.description: Optional. Metadata for the service. This data can be consumed by service clients. The entire metadata dictionary may contain up to 2000 characters, spread across all key-value pairs. Metadata that goes beyond any these limits will be rejected.

params.name: data.endpoints
params.description: Output only. Endpoints associated with this service. Returned on LookupService.Resolve. Control plane clients should use RegistrationService.ListEndpoints.
